</p></li><li id="LI_2CBBDB7085324353859D337889483F5E" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20. 
</p></li><li id="LI_A6898175F4B54A1EB14314B32674528A" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Spanner 7 mm. 
</p></li><li id="LI_07D2D9C733E64F699C417911EABD786B" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Allen key 2 mm. 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-9848D934-FF3E-4AC9-BA07-69028FA44036" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-1C6A5506-8461-4BFD-8B7C-FB47C7EF289A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2775D657-A2D0-4A2A-82D6-1E0449F632C7-low.png" id="IMAGE_9422B27C10994EBBA1C80124837A31D6" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2775D657-A2D0-4A2A-82D6-1E0449F632C7-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_7C9D95F7969F451881FF1C50D273FA49" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D079E38D-FF14-479C-AA22-4D9576D3E563-low.png" id="IMAGE_93DDCBD62D8A4854B559A37B3989F775" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D079E38D-FF14-479C-AA22-4D9576D3E563-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_B8AFEC1BCF63441ABC7ED222A94E21C0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_8A29F4589CA44F2A82B376980EDEC921" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the cover (7 screws). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_9993183F042B47ADA6C3AEF24B64F426" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-672FE2ED-757B-4139-97CB-E80DD2C0CACF-low.png" id="IMAGE_C9C4DC7491AC4214823329A09C1CF1DB" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-672FE2ED-757B-4139-97CB-E80DD2C0CACF-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_33C3134004774C76B92B2C247C557101" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AAA6FDC2-4750-4C8D-9B5C-8A610DD63344-low.png" id="IMAGE_B3766EF6152C42F4B5190A472EBE6227" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AAA6FDC2-4750-4C8D-9B5C-8A610DD63344-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_73E2F5C6BBC54A46A26D18D88CCFB7C5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D806FA76-B96C-4977-9F15-3A017DABBE89-low.png" id="IMAGE_9878FA734DB145D58F7214FB6F2D4706" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D806FA76-B96C-4977-9F15-3A017DABBE89-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_77A362E6B2ED4F33BAF1D5C7BADCFF32" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BB998929-D409-429B-B9AA-F97DE34A8A8E-low.png" id="IMAGE_1ABEDE2025B64399B178DA4EF5A4D8E9" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BB998929-D409-429B-B9AA-F97DE34A8A8E-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_02C9A39B3F9346BAA7C78E041CC57E7C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8119BD93-847D-451D-881F-6ABFADE07269-low.png" id="IMAGE_437419C9C5564686B064FCA6B5306738" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8119BD93-847D-451D-881F-6ABFADE07269-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the small cover (2 screws spanner 7 mm). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_F8BBB0E092B64989897C381BC9B4398A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-41428480-5D86-4EA3-A06E-FF1E08B0C3C9-low.png" id="IMAGE_7BB0019281EA4BAEA43D8DB822D99BA4" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-41428480-5D86-4EA3-A06E-FF1E08B0C3C9-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_2081440749A549D6B561EA4F5CB77370" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B9F0AEEF-B149-44E6-822E-F8CBC10ED6BE-low.png" id="IMAGE_2D17AE38C6F84E4185EC753948FC72C4" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B9F0AEEF-B149-44E6-822E-F8CBC10ED6BE-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the screw from the sensor. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Slide the sensor to the rear side. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the sensor. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_BBC52BBE7B0A41098969B6EF996B9EA6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DF511FCC-D693-4B27-9C74-B3ED0480519A-low.png" id="IMAGE_E4073A823E214C42B64AFE16DF612C7E" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DF511FCC-D693-4B27-9C74-B3ED0480519A-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_BFF2A794F4304DB6935FCA9B27F15699" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-540A1C90-9147-47CB-8E17-EF6FF377F89B-low.png" id="IMAGE_5AA69F4619964F40831F184BCEE79E93" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-540A1C90-9147-47CB-8E17-EF6FF377F89B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Loosen the 2 small allen screws on the axis. 
</p><note id="GUID-F25F3487-6B3F-4386-81B4-85988E55E8F8" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Be careful not to loosen the screws. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_ECC1362EC6C046E5AB361FC155547D35" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0C57EA9C-9EC3-4B16-A3D8-CBE95DE6E01E-low.png" id="IMAGE_CD8B137740F743B08B007D216683F239" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0C57EA9C-9EC3-4B16-A3D8-CBE95DE6E01E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the connector of the sensor. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-EFC0447F-2051-482F-AF47-164FF4FBE4C5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D4F4F666-4E62-493D-8AC0-41F660FE54A4-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D4F4F666-4E62-493D-8AC0-41F660FE54A4-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_64EC1E4C7D67427C8153883B283AD29B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0024159D-05FB-4D6D-B4CD-2B7C12F8B42B-low.png" id="IMAGE_AC2C094DA6DC466E8EBACCA94BD16BB8" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0024159D-05FB-4D6D-B4CD-2B7C12F8B42B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 2 screws of the sensor. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_EB30121C0773491EBD0BB15744C4BD3D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FF78550B-7176-4405-B5FB-9A9D73508D97-low.png" id="IMAGE_F0EA632184644035B0895F580B7B6A08" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FF78550B-7176-4405-B5FB-9A9D73508D97-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the sensor from the axis. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_D90C51466A584E99B1AD4096F1483C3B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E1B38B5D-3E67-424C-A7C5-F3237B2A3B62-low.png" id="IMAGE_39FC91978E794467BAE9E04F06DD081A" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E1B38B5D-3E67-424C-A7C5-F3237B2A3B62-low.png"/></fig><fig id="FIG_9EB5459126F44A76BC95490931F33EB2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D079E38D-FF14-479C-AA22-4D9576D3E563-low.png" id="IMAGE_0F19EEFE0DF04908BDCE1778F5C45E1C" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D079E38D-FF14-479C-AA22-4D9576D3E563-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_A7B7F2276EC64F88A303AD9C9A521E96" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Install in reverse order. 
</p><note id="GUID-497B1D95-0EDE-4880-BA60-05304DF94700" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Position the sensor (with the 2 screws) in the middle position of the slotted holes. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect the Service jumper, exit SDS and press 'Restart' on the operator panel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Always do the following calibration : 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="SDS21-6-002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-D650BDBB-4674-4B96-BD64-98FDD9BAF4CB.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 21-6-002 Select required printer calibrations [Special Tests]?>21-6-002 Select required printer calibrations [Special Tests]</xref> and select: <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">Media transport calibration</ph> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="SDS21-6-003" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-B828E436-A124-4809-981E-2DBE1E09A388.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 21-6-003 Execute selected printer calibrations [Special Tests]?>21-6-003 Execute selected printer calibrations [Special Tests]</xref> 
</p></li></ul></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-027A0565-F050-4419-9B19-C5C075964C5A.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
